Sentencas: We synthesized Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) powders with a primary particle size of 20 nm using a Pechini type method.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sc0.1Zr0.9O1.95 composite cathode on zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By using nanocrystalline BSCF powders, we were able to fabricate a ceria interlayer-free nanoporous cathode on a scandia stabilized zirconia (ScSZ) electrolyte at low temperatures.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sc0.1Zr0.9O1.95 composite cathode on zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Cathodes sintered below 750 degrees C lacked sufficient mechanical adhesion to the electrolyte, while electrode was well adhered to the electrolyte when fired at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sc0.1Zr0.9O1.95 composite cathode on zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The symmetrical BSCF-ScSZ vertical bar yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ)vertical bar BSCF-ScSZ half-cell that we generated had an exceptionally low polarization resistance of 0.06 Omega.cm(2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sc0.1Zr0.9O1.95 composite cathode on zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the BSCF-ScSZ vertical bar ScSZ vertical bar Ni-ScSZ unit cell was over 1 W cm(-2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sc0.1Zr0.9O1.95 composite cathode on zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: We investigated the durability of the BSCF-ScSZ composite cathode by 30 thermo-cycles performed by varying the temperature from 200 to 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sc0.1Zr0.9O1.95 composite cathode on zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance after the test remained low at less than 0.08 Omega.cm(2).
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sc0.1Zr0.9O1.95 composite cathode on zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
